    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.charcoalpile.name=Запал угольной ямы
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.charcoalpile.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCharcoal Pile Igniter, CPI§r\nConverts Logs into Brittle Charcoal blocks\nAutomatically starts when formed\n§5100 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.charcoalpile.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63-13§7x§63-7§7x§63-13§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Top layer, directly touching a wood log\n   Can be up to 13x7x13 in size, including the dirt; shape doesn't matter\n§f   Dirt/Grass: §7Top and middle layers, covering wood logs\n§f   Bricks: §7Bottom layer, under all wood logs\n§f   Wood Logs: §7Up to 5 layers, inside the previously mentioned blocks\n   No air between logs allowed.\n   All logs must be within 6 x/z of the controller, so it must be dead-center for a full 11x11 square of wood.\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.chemicalreactor.name=Большой химический реактор
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.chemicalreactor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eChemical Reactor, LCR§r\nAccepts fluids instead of fluid cells\n§bMachine does not lose efficiency when overclocked\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.chemicalreactor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   8x§7 - §622x §r§7Chemically Inert Machine Casing\n§f   PTFE Pipe Machine Casing: §7Center\n§f   Heating Coil: §7Adjacent to the PTFE Pipe Machine Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any casing\n   You can have multiple hatches/buses\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.cleanroom.name=Контроллер чистой комнаты
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.cleanroom.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCleanroom§r\nConsumes 40 EU/t when first turned on, and 4 EU/t once at 100% efficiency\nCan accept 2A from an LV energy hatch\nWill overclock and gain efficiency faster starting from HV\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§cWarning:\nBelow 100% efficiency machines inside have a chance to void outputs!\nEach maintenance issue reduces maximum efficiency by 10%\nGenerating any pollution inside causes the cleanroom to shut down\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.cleanroom.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63-15§7x§64-15§7x§63-15§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Top center\n     If width or length is even, it can be in either of the two middle positions\n§f   Filter Machine Casing: §7Top layer, except for edges\n§f   Plascrete Blocks: §7Edges of top layer, all walls and floor. Minimum §620§7.\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Plascrete Block. Exactly one\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Plascrete Block. Exactly one\n   \n   Up to §630%§7 of plascrete blocks can be replaced by other valid blocks\n   Try some of the following:\n   - Any §8EV+§7 tier glass\n   - Machine hulls or diodes for item and power transfer\n   - Reinforced Doors (§oIC2§r§7). Keep closed, no gaps allowed or efficiency will drop!\n   - Elevators (§oOpenBlocks§r§7) or Travel Anchors (§oEnderIO§r§7)\n   See §8config/GregTech/MachineStats.cfg§7 for more valid blocks\n   §eAll non-plascrete blocks now share the same limit. Feel free to mix and match!\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.cokeoven.name=Коксовая печь
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.cokeoven.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCoke Oven§r\nTurns coal into coke and produces creosote oil\n§510 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§l§6§bJ§du§fl§di§ba§6§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.cokeoven.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   0x§7 - §626x §r§7Coke Oven Casing\n   §fCoke Oven Hatch: §7Any Coke Oven Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.concretebackfiller1.name=Бетонный заполнитель
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.concretebackfiller1.tooltip=Machine Type: §eConcrete Backfiller§r\nWill fill in areas below it with light concrete. This goes through walls\nUse it to remove any spawning locations beneath your base to reduce lag\nWill pull back the pipes after it finishes that layer\nRange is 16x16 blocks horizontally\nMinimum energy hatch tier: §6MV§r\nBase cycle time: 3 seconds\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.concretebackfiller1.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§67§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§f   Solid Steel Machine Casing: §7form the 3x1x3 Base\n§f   Solid Steel Machine Casing: §71x3x1 pillar above the center of the base (2 minimum total)\n§f   Steel Frame Boxes: §7Each pillar's side and 1x3x1 on top\n§f   Energy Hatch: §71x MV+, Any base casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any base casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Mining Pipes, optional, any base casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7GT Concrete, any base casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Mining Pipes, optional, any base casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
