    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.concretebackfiller3.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§67§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§f   Stable Titanium Machine Casing: §7form the 3x1x3 Base\n§f   Stable Titanium Machine Casing: §71x3x1 pillar above the center of the base (2 minimum total)\n§f   Titanium Frame Boxes: §7Each pillar's side and 1x3x1 on top\n§f   Energy Hatch: §71x EV+, Any base casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any base casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Mining Pipes, optional, any base casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7GT Concrete, any base casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Mining Pipes, optional, any base casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.cracker.name=Установка крекинга нефти
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.cracker.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCracker, OCU§r\n§b-10%§7 EU Usage per §fHeating Coil§7 Tier\nMaximum of §b50%§7 EU discount\nThermally cracks heavy hydrocarbons into lighter fractions\nMore efficient than the Chemical Reactor\nGives different benefits whether it hydro or steam-cracks:\nHydro - Consumes 20% less Hydrogen and outputs 25% more cracked fluid\nSteam - Outputs 50% more cracked fluid\n(Values compared to cracking in the Chemical Reactor)\nPlace the appropriate circuit in the controller or an input bus\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.cracker.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§63§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   18x§7 - §621x §r§7Clean Stainless Steel Machine Casing\n§f   2 Rings of 8 Coils: §7Each side of the controller\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7For cracking fluid (Steam/Hydrogen/etc.) ONLY, Any middle ring casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any left/right side casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any right/left side casing\n   Input/Output Hatches must be on opposite sides!\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any middle ring casing, optional for programmed circuit automation\n   Uses sub channel §6coil§r§7 for §6Heating Coils Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.decay-warehouse.name=Промышленное радиоизотопное хранилище
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.decay-warehouse.tooltip=Machine Type: §eDecay Warehouse§r\nStores a single type of radioactive isotope and allows it to decay over time\nDecay speed is dependent on the isotopes' half-lives (lower is faster)\nIsotopes decay regardless of whether the warehouse is on or powered\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nThe warehouse's capacity equals the super chest's capacity divided by §9400§7.\nThe warehouse will pull in up to §9N / 512§7 items per second,\nwhere §9N§7 is the warehouse's EU input (standard energy hatch rules)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nRight click the controller with a screwdriver to dump stored isotopes into the output bus\nRight click the controller with a plunger to empty it\nThe warehouse's contents are §c§nvoided§7 when the controller is broken\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
