    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.heatexchanger.name=Большой теплообменник
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.heatexchanger.tooltip=Machine Type: §eHeat Exchanger, LHE§r\nInputs are §cLava§7, §cHot Coolant§7, or §cHot Solar Salt\nOutputs are §9Pahoehoe Lava§7, §9IC2 Coolant§7, or §9Cold Solar Salt\nConverts distilled water into §rSteam§7 or §rSH Steam§7 in the process\nOutputs §rSH Steam§7 if the input rate of hot fluid is above a certain §dthreshold\nExplodes after 100s if it runs out of distilled water\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§cLava§7 | SH Threshold §d1,000 mB/s§7 | Max Input §c2,000 mB/s§7 | Max Output §r8,000 mB/t SH Steam\n§cHot Coolant§7 | SH Threshold §d800 mB/s§7 | Max Input §c1,600 mB/s§7 | Max Output §r16,000 mB/t SH Steam\n§cHot Solar Salt§7 | SH Threshold §d160 mB/s§7 | Max Input §c320 mB/s§7 | Max Output §r16,000 mB/t SH Steam\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nA circuit in the controller lowers the SH threshold at the cost of steam\n§d-3.75%§7 SH Threshold and §r-1.5%§7 steam output per circuit over 1\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.heatexchanger.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§64§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   20x§7 - §628x §r§7Stable Titanium Machine Casing\n§f   Titanium Pipe Casing: §7Center 2 blocks\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hot Fluid, bottom center casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Distilled Water, any casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Cold Fluid, top center casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Steam/SH Steam, any casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.hipcompressor.name=Установка для горячей изостатической опрессовки
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.hipcompressor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCompressor, HIP§r\nHIP Unit heats up while running\nWhen it reaches maximum heat, it becomes §4§loverheated!\nThis is only resolved by letting the machine fully cool down\nWhen §4overheated§7, recipes are slowed down drastically\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nSome recipes §lrequire§r§7 HIP\nIf the machine is §4overheated§7 when one of these recipes starts, it will be voided!\nRead the current heat using Heat Sensor Hatches\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nMore advanced coils allow better heat control - the unit will take longer to overheat\nUnit heats by §a(5% x 0.90 ^ (Coil Tier - 1))§7 every second while running\nUnit cools by §a2%§7 base every second while not running\nCooling rate increases by an additional §a2%§7 for each second since running\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n250% §cfaster§7/§9slower§7 than singleblock machines of the same voltage\nUses §c75%§7/§9110%§7 the EU/t normally required\nGains §c4§7/§91§7 parallels per voltage tier\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§a§lOllie§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.hipcompressor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §615§7x§610§7x§67§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   95x §r§7Electric Compressor Casing (minimum)\n§6   60x §r§7Compressor Pipe Casing (minimum)\n§6   12x §r§7Coolant Duct\n§6   12x §r§7Heating Duct\n§6   22x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n§6   30x §r§7Coil (tiered)\n§f   Heat Sensor Hatch: §7Any Electric Compressor Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Pipe Casings on Side\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Pipe Casings on Side\n§f   Output Bus: §7Pipe Casings on Side\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Electric Compressor Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Electric Compressor Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6coil§r§7 for §6Heating Coils Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.implosioncompressor.name=Имплозионный компрессор
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.implosioncompressor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eImplosion Compressor§r\nExplosions are fun\n§510000 §7Pollution per second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.implosioncompressor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §63§7x§63§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   16x§7 - §624x §r§7Solid Steel Machine Casing\n   Casings can be replaced with Explosion Hazard Signs\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.industrialfarm.name=Промышленная ферма
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.industrialfarm.tooltip=Machine Type: §eIndustrial Crop Cultivator, IF§r\nGrows crops at an industrial scale\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nThe §blength§7 of the machine depends on the §ctier§7 of the §fSeed Bed§7\nThe §ctier§7 of the §fupgrades§7 must match the §ctier§7 of the §fSeed Bed§7\nEnergy Hatch limited by §fGlass§7 Tier\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp Hatches when using an Overclocked Growth Accelerator Upgrade!§r\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.industrialfarm.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§64§7x§63-14§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n§6   18x§7 - §640x §r§7Bricked Agricultural Casing\n§6   0x§7 - §612x §r§7Wood Frame Box\n§6   3x§7 - §636x §r§7Seed Bed (tiered)\n§f   Upgrades (tiered): §7Any wooden frame boxes\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any casing with hint number 1\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any casing with hint number 1\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any casing with hint number 1\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing with hint number 1\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any casing with hint number 1\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6if_tier§r§7 for §6Controls the tier of the Industrial Farm\n   Uses sub channel §6if_upgrade§r§7 for §6Enables upgrade placement for the Industrial Farm\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.large-hadron-collider.name=Большой адронный коллайдер
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.large-hadron-collider.tooltip=Machine Type: §eParticle Accelerator, Particle Collider, LHC§r\nAccelerates particles to high energies and then collides them to generate new particles\nElectrically neutral particles are unaffected\nSet the §etarget beam energy§7 (up to 2TeV) and the §9maximum number of cycles§7\nCycles every second\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§f§nAccelerator mode§7\nAccelerates the beam in the smaller LHC ring\nAccelerator mode increases the §6Beam Energy§7 by §bEU Consumed in cycle§7 * §f0.1eV§7, until the\n§eTarget Beam Energy§7 is reached, or the §9maximum number of cycles§7 is reached\nIf the §eTarget Beam Energy§7 is reached, multiply the current §cBeam Rate§7 by §f1.1§7\n§aPower§7 cost starts at §f1A§7 of §fUV§7 per §cBeam Rate§7 and increases quadratically\nwith the §dnumber of completed cycles§7\n§aP§7 = §f(1A UV)§7 * §cR§7 * §dN§7^2\nAutomatically switches to Collider mode when the §9maximum number of cycles§7 is reached\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§f§nCollider mode§7\nSplits the beam into §ftwo§7 beams that go in opposite directions in the larger LHC ring, which\nthen collide to generate new particles\nThe §3Collision Energy§7 is two times the §6Beam Energy§7\nIf the §3Collision Energy§7 exceeds the rest mass of a particle, that particle will start\nappearing in the outputs\nA particle output can only appear in the modules that correspond to the forces that\ninteract with that particle\nFor example, Neutrinos cannot appear in the Strong force module, §fALICE§7, since they do\nnot interact via the strong force\n§fFiltered Beamline Output Hatches§7 will allow you to see the list of possible outputs, and\nfilter them\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nThere are four LHC modules, marked by the letter on top of the module:\n§bE - Electromagnetism§7 - Charged Matter Sensor (§bCMS§7)\n§2W - Weak Interaction§7 - Advanced Total Lepton Assimilation Snare (§2ATLAS§7)\n§fS - Strong Force§7 - Absolute Lattice Integrated Chromodynamic Encapsulator (§fALICE§7)\n§5G - Gravity§7 - Localized Horizon Curvature Binder (§5LHCb§7)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §aAuthor: §6Ham§fCorp§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.large-hadron-collider.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §6109§7x§613§7x§6122§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   6034x §r§7Collider Casing\n§6   1x §r§7Energy Hatch\n§6   16x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Casing\n§6   20x §r§7Shielded Accelerator Glass\n§6   1x §r§7Beamline Input Hatch\n§6   73x §r§7Neonite (Any, optional)\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.large-neutralization-engine.name=Large Neutralization Engine
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.large-neutralization-engine.tooltip=Machine Type: §eAcid Generator, LNE§r\n(Dis)solves all your problems!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nCan §fuse §7a §bbase §7to boost §defficiency §7(consumes one by one):\n§bSodium Hydroxide§7 : §d150%§7 : §f60§7/minute\n§bPotassium Hydroxide§7 : §d190%§7 : §f24§7/minute\n§bCaesium Hydroxide§7 : §d250%§7 : §f6§7/minute\n§bFrancium Hydroxide§7 : §d500%§7 : §f5§7/minute\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nProduces §cToxic Residue §7from burning acids\nIf the §cToxic Residue §7exceeds the §3Capacity§7, the multiblock will §4EXPLODE!\nEvery §ftick§7, §cToxic Residue §7will §fincrease §7by §6Residue Rate§7*§eFuel Consumption(L/t)§7*rand(§f0.5§7-§f1.5§7)\n§6Residue Rate §7is calculated as §f0.05§7*(§dFuel Value (EU/L)§7)^§f0.8\nEvery §ftick§7, §cToxic Residue §7will §fdecrease §7by §9Base Decay§7*§eDecay Boost§7*(§cToxic Residue§7^§f0.08§7)\nResidue will decay §f10 §7times slower when multiblock is disabled\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nInsert §dRobot Arms §7to increase §eDecay Boost§7:\n§eDecay Boost §7is calculated as §f1.2§7^§dRobot Arm Tier §7if §aIV§7 or below, §f1.4§7^§dRobot Arm Tier §7if §dLuV§7 or above\nInsert §dmultiple §7(§f16§7 max) robot arms to multiply §eDecay Boost §7by sqrt(§dRobot Arm Amount§7)\nEvery §fminute§7, 1/(§f45§7*(1+§dRobot Arm Tier§7))chance for §fall §7used robot arms to §cvoid\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nStructure has §f3 Tiers§7, §fTier §7determines §9Base Decay §7and §3Capacity§7:\n§fT1§7 : §fStrengthened Inanimate Machine Casing§7 : §9200§7 : §3375,000\n§fT2§7 : §fPrecise Stationary Machine Casing§7 : §9400§7 : §31,000,000\n§fT3§7 : §fUltimate Static Machine Casing§7 : §9700§7 : §32,500,000\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.large-neutralization-engine.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §611§7x§67§7x§63§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Top center\n§6   30x§7 - §646x §r§7Tiered Casings\n§6   34x §r§7Polytetrafluoroethylene Frame Box\n§6   15x §r§7PTFE Pipe Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Tiered Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Tiered Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Tiered Casing\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Any Tiered Casing\n§f   Toxic Residue Sensor Hatch: §7Any Tiered Casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
