    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pyro.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§64§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   60x§7 - §680x §r§7Pyrolyse Oven Casing\n§f   Heating Coils: §7Center 3x1x3 of the bottom layer\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Center 3x1x3 area in top layer\n§f   Input Bus: §7Center 3x1x3 area in top layer\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Center 3x1x3 area in top layer\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any bottom layer casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n   Uses sub channel §6coil§r§7 for §6Heating Coils Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.pyro.tooltip_secondary.15546=§fDimensions: §67§7x§66§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   60x §r§7Pyrolyse Oven Casing (minimum)\n§6   12x §r§7Heating Coils (tiered)\n§6   2x §r§7Steel Frame Box\n§6   8x §r§7Steel Pipe Casing\n§6   4x §r§7Steel Firebox Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n§f   Muffler Hatch: §7Any top layer casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any top layer casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any top layer casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any bottom layer casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any bottom layer casing\n   Uses sub channel §6coil§r§7 for §6Heating Coils Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.reallybigheatexchanger.name=XL Теплообменник
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.reallybigheatexchanger.tooltip=Machine Type: §eHeat Exchanger, WWXL§r\nEquivalent to 32 Large Heat Exchangers\nInputs are §cLava§7, §cHot Coolant§7, or §cHot Solar Salt\nOutputs are §9Pahoehoe Lava§7, §9IC2 Coolant§7, or §9Cold Solar Salt\nConverts distilled water into §rSteam§7 or §rSH Steam§7 in the process\nOutputs §rSH Steam§7 if the input rate of hot fluid is above a certain §dthreshold\nExplodes immediately if it runs out of distilled water\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§cLava§7 | SH Threshold §d32,000 mB/s§7 | Max Input §c64,000 mB/s§7 | Max Output §r256,000 mB/t SH Steam\n§cHot Coolant§7 | SH Threshold §d25,600 mB/s§7 | Max Input §c51,200 mB/s§7 | Max Output §r512,000 mB/t SH Steam\n§cHot Solar Salt§7 | SH Threshold §d5,120 mB/s§7 | Max Input §c10,240 mB/s§7 | Max Output §r512,000 mB/t SH Steam\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nA circuit in the controller lowers the SH threshold at the cost of steam\n§d-3.75%§7 SH Threshold and §r-1.5%§7 steam output per circuit over 1\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.reallybigheatexchanger.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§69§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center, 4th layer\n§6   90x §r§7Reinforced Heat Exchanger Casing (minimum)\n§f   Tungstensteel Pipe Casing: §7Center 3x5x3 (45 blocks)\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Hot fluid, bottom center casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Distilled water, any bottom layer casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Cold fluid, top center casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Steam/SH Steam, any bottom layer casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.solarfactory.name=Солнечная фабрика
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.solarfactory.tooltip=Machine Type: §eSolar Factory§r\nController block for the Solar Factory\nProduces solar panels in bulk\nThe structure has 3 tiers, each allowing greater production than the last\n§f§lTier §b§l2§f§l and above:\n§a  Supports Multi-Amp energy hatches\n  25% more outputs for every Wafer tier used above the minimum required\n  The bonus to output occurs after parallels, and cannot be greater than 100%\n  The recipes shown in NEI display the minimum wafer tier required\n  LV-LuV Solar Panels can be made without the previous panel, but at a higher cost\n  §fPrecise Casing§7 Tier determines §6Parallels§7\n  §aMk-I§7/§9MK-II§7/§dMK-III§7/§6MK-IV§7->§a8§7/§916§7/§d32§7/§664§7 Parallels\n§f§lTier §b§l3§f§l:\n§a  Supports Laser energy hatches\n  ZPM-UV Solar Panels can be made without the previous panel, but at a higher cost\n  Bonus per increased wafer tier is raised to 50%\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§fPure§bB§3l§9u§1ez§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.solarfactory.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §67§7x§610§7x§69§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n   §f§lTier §b§l1:\n§6   15x§7 - §641x §r§7Clean Stainless Steel Machine Casing\n§6   24x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n§6   20x §r§7Damascus Steel Frame Box\n   §f§lTier §b§l2:\n§6   35x§7 - §6101x §r§7Tungstensteel Machine Casing\n§6   74x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n§6   75x §r§7Tungsten Frame Box\n§6   20x §r§7Precise Electronic Unit Casing (tiered)\n   §f§lTier §b§l3:\n§6   50x§7 - §6140x §r§7Advanced Iridium Machine Casing\n§6   67x §r§7Any Tiered Glass\n§6   24x §r§7Tungsten Frame Box\n§6   26x §r§7Precise Electronic Unit Casing (tiered)\n§6   6x §r§7Black Plutonium Item Pipe\n   §f§lAll Tiers: \n   §fImprecise Unit Casings cannot be used\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Machine Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Machine Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Machine Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Machine Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Machine Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6unit_casing§r§7 for §6Precise Electronic Unit Casing Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.solidifier.name=Промышленный отвердитель
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.solidifier.tooltip=Machine Type: §eFluid Solidifier§r\n§4DEPRECATED - Controller will be removed in next major update!\n§4Check NEI for new Controller and conversion recipe\nCan use §eSolidifier Hatches§7 to hold different molds\n§62§7 Parallels per §fVoltage§7 Tier\nGains §63§7 Parallels per §fVoltage §7Tier per width expansion\nSpeeds up to a maximum of §a300%§7\nDecays at double the rate that it speeds up at\n§b80%§7 EU Usage\nEnergy Hatch limited by §fGlass§7 Tier, §c§l§nUMV§7-tier unlocks all\n§9Pretty Ⱄⱁⰾⰻⰴ, isn't it\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines\nAdded by: §a§9Omda§cCZ§r§7
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.solidifier.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §69-33§7x§65§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) §c(Hollow)\n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§6   91x§7 - §6211x §r§7Solidifier Casing\n§6   13x§7 - §673x §r§7Solidifier Radiator\n§6   4x§7 - §616x §r§7Heat Proof Machine Casing\n§6   4x§7 - §616x §r§7Clean Stainless Steel Machine Casing\n§6   14x§7 - §6117x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.spinmatron.name=Спинматрон-2737
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.spinmatron.tooltip=Machine Type: §eCentrifuge§r\n3 Modes: §dLight§7 | §6Standard§7 | §aHeavy\nOverclocks limited to §fHatch Tier + 1\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\nThis machine can run recipes regardless of tier, if given enough energy\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nGains §f2§7 Turbine Slots per Structure Tier\n§64§7 Parallels per §fSum of Turbine§7 Tier\nNon-Huge Turbines have reduced effectiveness...\n§a300%§7 Speed\n§b70%§7 EU Usage\nRequires Recipe Tier * §910L/s§7 of §5Kerosene§7 to operate by default\nSupply §5Biocatalyzed Propulsion Fluid§7 instead for a §f1.25x §7Parallel multiplier\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§dLight Mode§7: +§d100%§7 Speed Bonus, Maximum Recipe Tier is §dVoltage Tier - 3\n§6Standard Mode§7: No Changes\n§aHeavy Mode§7: Divides Parallels by §a32§7, Requires T3+ Structure and §5Biocatalyzed Propulsion Fluid\nMultiplies EU Cost by §c16\nSome recipes §c§lrequire§a Heavy Mode\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\n§o§4Maahes guides the way...\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.spinmatron.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §617§7x§617§7x§617§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   81x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§6   550x §r§7Vibration-Safe Casing (minimum)\n§6   144x §r§7Chamber Grate\n§6   9x §r§7Central Frame Blocks (tiered)\n§6   56x §r§7Central Rotor Blocks (tiered)\n§6   54x §r§7IsaMill Gearbox Casing\n§6   160x §r§7PBI Pipe Casing\n§6   24x §r§7Turbine Shaft\n§6   8x §r§7Rotor Assembly\n§6   264x §r§7SC Turbine Casing\n§f   Input Bus: §7Any Vibration-Safe Casing\n§f   Output Bus: §7Any Vibration-Safe Casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Any Vibration-Safe Casing\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Any Vibration-Safe Casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any Vibration-Safe Casing\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any Vibration-Safe Casing\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.supercapacitor.name=Лазуротроновый суперконденсатор
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.supercapacitor.tooltip=Machine Type: §eEnergy Storage, LSC§r\nLoses energy equal to 1% of the total capacity every 24 hours\nCapped at §c1,000,000§7 EU/t passive loss per §4§nUHV§7 capacitor\nThe passive loss increases §4100§7-fold for every capacitor tier above\nPassive loss is multiplied by the number of maintenance issues present\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nGlass shell has to be Tier - 3 of the highest capacitor tier\n§aSupports TecTech Multi-Amp and Laser Hatches!\n§2§nUV§7-tier §fGlass§7 required for §9Tec§1Tech§7 Laser Hatches\nAdd more or better capacitors to increase capacity\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nWireless mode can be enabled by right clicking with a screwdriver\nThis mode can only be enabled if you have a §4§nUHV§7+ capacitor in the multiblock.\nWhen enabled every §96,000§7 ticks the LSC will attempt to re-balance against your\nwireless EU network.\nIf there is less than §c6e13§7(§4§nUHV§7) EU in the LSC\nit will withdraw from the network and add to the LSC.\nIf there is more it will add §4§l§nall excess§r§7 EU to the network, removing it from the LSC\nThis can potentially brick your base, be careful\nThe threshold increases §4100§7-fold for every capacitor tier above\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.supercapacitor.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§64-50§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   Modular height of 4-50 blocks.\n   §fController: §7Front bottom center\n§f   Lapotronic Super Capacitor Casing: §75x2x5 base (at least 17x)\n§f   Lapotronic Capacitor (§8EV§7-§2§nUV§7), Ultimate Capacitor (§4§nUHV§7-§c§l§nUMV§7): §7Center 3x(1-47)x3 above base (9-423 blocks)\n   You can also use the Empty Capacitor to save materials if you use it for less than half the blocks\n§6   41x§7 - §6777x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (tiered)\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Dynamo Hatch: §7Any casing\n§f   Laser Target/Source Hatches: §7Any casing, must be using §2§nUV§7-tier glass\n   You can have several I/O Hatches\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6capacitor§r§7 for §6Capacitor Tier if specified. Otherwise pick any acceptable capacitor.\n   Uses sub channel §6height§r§7 for §6Structure Height\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any casing\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.tfft.name=T.F.F.T
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.tfft.tooltip=Machine Type: §eFluid Tank§r\nHigh-Tech fluid tank that can hold up to 25 different fluids!\nHas 1/25th of the total capacity as capacity for each fluid\nRight clicking the controller with a screwdriver will turn on excess voiding\nFluid storage amount and running cost depends on the storage field blocks used\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nNote on hatch locking:\nUse an Integrated Circuit in the GUI slot to limit which fluid is output\nThe index of a stored fluid can be obtained through the Tricorder\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.tfft.tooltip_secondary=§fDimensions: §65§7x§65-15§7x§65§7 (§6W§7x§6H§7x§6L§7) \n§fStructure: \n   §fController: §7Front center\n§6   20x §r§7T.F.F.T Casing (minimum)\n§6   7x§7 - §6117x §r§7Storage Field Blocks (tiered)\n   Energy hatch is not required when running cost is 0\n§6   48x§7 - §6208x §r§7Any Tiered Glass (EV+)\n§f   Maintenance Hatch: §7Any top or bottom casing\n§f   Energy Hatch: §7Any top or bottom casing\n§f   Input Hatch: §7Instead of any casing or glass, has to touch storage field block\n§f   Output Hatch: §7Instead of any casing or glass, has to touch storage field block\n   You can have a bunch of hatches\n§f   Multi I/O Hatches: §7Instead of any casing or glass, has to touch storage field block\n   Use MIOH with conduits or fluid storage buses to see all fluids at once.\n   Uses sub channel §6glass§r§7 for §6Glass Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6field§r§7 for §6Storage Field Tier\n   Uses sub channel §6height§r§7 for §6Structure Height\n   §7§m------------------------------\n§fTo see the structure, use a§9 Structure§1Lib §r§fHologram Projector on the Controller!
    S:gt.blockmachines.multimachine.tm.microwave.tooltip=Machine Type: §eMicrowave Grinder§r\nController block of the Microwave Grinder\nStarts a timer when enabled\nWhile the timer is running anything inside the machine will take damage\nThe machine will also collect any items inside of it\nCan be configured with a Parametrizer\n(Do not insert a Wither)\n§7§m-----------------------------------------\nHold §l[LSHIFT]§r§7 to display structure guidelines
